<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 11513/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Bryan</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-03"><hi rend="italic">February 3,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bacon informs Mr. Bryan that the President has sent to the young
                            King and to the bereaved Queen Mother a personal message of sympathy,
                            and directs him to tender to the Portuguese Government through the usual
                            channels the condolence and sympathetic sorrow of the people of the
                            United States. In the absence of Mr. Root Mr. Bryan is requested to
                            convey to the minister for foreign affairs adequate expression of Mr.
                            Bacon’s personal sentiments.)</p>
                    </div>
